","inLanguage":"fr-FR","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"fr-FR"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/lassistanat-etudiant-et-les-roles-de-soutien-en-turquie/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/lassistanat-etudiant-et-les-roles-de-soutien-en-turquie/","name":"L&#039;Assistanat Étudiant et les Rôles de Soutien en Turquie - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-03-24T11:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-24T11:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"fr-FR"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"fr-FR"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"L&#039;Assistanat Étudiant et les Rôles de Soutien en Turquie - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-03-24T11:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-03-24T11:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Soutien et Réussite Académiques","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Découvrez les opportunités d&#039;assistanat étudiant et de soutien académique en Turquie. Explorez dès maintenant ces postes pour enrichir votre parcours et orienter votre carrière !","name":"L&#039;Assistanat Étudiant et les Rôles de Soutien en Turquie - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/lassistanat-etudiant-et-les-roles-de-soutien-en-turquie/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/lassistanat-etudiant-et-les-roles-de-soutien-en-turquie/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"fr-FR","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/fr/lassistanat-etudiant-et-les-roles-de-soutien-en-turquie/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<h2 id="turkiyede-ogrenci-asistanligi-nedir" class="wp-block-heading">Qu&#8217;est-ce que l&#8217;assistanat étudiant en Turquie ?</h2>
<div id="model-response-message-contentr_ee08f69aeebec094" class="markdown markdown-main-panel stronger enable-updated-hr-color" dir="ltr">
<p>En Turquie, l&#8217;<b>assistanat étudiant</b> est un programme qui offre aux étudiants universitaires l&#8217;opportunité d&#8217;acquérir de l&#8217;expérience dans des unités à la fois académiques et administratives. Les étudiants peuvent travailler à temps partiel dans diverses facultés, départements, bibliothèques ou centres de recherche de l&#8217;université, et ainsi soutenir leur parcours éducatif.</p>
<h3>Objectif et missions de l&#8217;assistanat étudiant</h3>
<p>L&#8217;assistanat étudiant ne se contente pas de fournir un soutien financier aux étudiants, il contribue également à leur développement professionnel et personnel. Les missions peuvent varier en fonction du département dans lequel ils travaillent. Cependant, elles incluent généralement :</p>
<ul>
<li><b>Soutien académique :</b> Aider les membres du corps professoral à préparer le matériel de cours, dans les travaux de laboratoire ou les projets de recherche.</li>
<li><b>Soutien administratif :</b> Participer aux tâches de bureau (comme le classement, la saisie de données), au sein des services des affaires étudiantes ou dans l&#8217;organisation d&#8217;événements universitaires.</li>
<li><b>Services centrés sur l&#8217;étudiant :</b> Apporter un soutien aux étudiants dans les bibliothèques, les centres d&#8217;orientation ou les services pour étudiants en situation de handicap.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Conditions de candidature et de travail</h3>
<p>Chaque université a ses propres directives concernant l&#8217;assistanat étudiant, et les conditions de candidature sont définies selon ces règles. Généralement, des conditions telles qu&#8217;avoir une moyenne supérieure à un certain seuil, ne pas avoir de sanction disciplinaire et être étudiant à temps plein sont requises.</p>
<ul>
<li><b>Durée du travail :</b> Les heures de travail des assistants étudiants sont généralement limitées sur une base hebdomadaire ou mensuelle.</li>
<li><b>Rémunération :</b> Le paiement est effectué sur la base d&#8217;un taux horaire. Ce taux peut varier d&#8217;une université à l&#8217;autre ou selon le salaire minimum horaire fixé pour la période.</li>
<li><b>Avantages :</b> Grâce à ce programme, les étudiants développent un réseau professionnel au sein de l&#8217;université et se préparent à la vie active après l&#8217;obtention de leur diplôme.</li>
</ul>
<p>L&#8217;assistanat étudiant offre également aux étudiants qui visent une carrière académique l&#8217;opportunité de connaître de près les membres du corps professoral et de développer leurs compétences en recherche. Si l&#8217;assistanat étudiant vous intéresse, la meilleure démarche est de suivre les annonces des services compétents de votre université (Bureau des affaires étudiantes ou services administratifs).</p>
</div>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph"><span style="color: revert; font-family: inherit; font-size: 35px; font-style: inherit;">Processus de candidature et exigences pour l&#8217;assistanat étudiant en Turquie</span></p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Les étudiants souhaitant devenir assistants étudiants en Turquie doivent suivre un processus de candidature spécifique. Ce processus comprend généralement les étapes suivantes :</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Documents requis</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Formulaire de candidature :</strong> Le formulaire à remplir pour le programme d&#8217;assistanat étudiant de l&#8217;université.</li>
<li><strong>CV :</strong> Un curriculum vitae à jour incluant votre parcours scolaire, vos compétences et vos expériences.</li>
<li><strong>Relevé de notes :</strong> Le document montrant les notes des cours que vous avez suivis.</li>
<li><strong>Lettres de recommandation :</strong> Des recommandations de la part de membres du corps professoral ou d&#8217;employeurs.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Étapes de la candidature</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Contactez le département concerné :</strong> Avant de postuler, contactez le département qui vous intéresse pour vous informer sur les postes vacants.</li>
<li><strong>Préparez vos documents :</strong> Rassemblez tous les documents mentionnés ci-dessus sans en oublier.</li>
<li><strong>Soumettez votre candidature :</strong> Déposez votre candidature dans les délais impartis et participez au processus d&#8217;entretien si nécessaire.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="ogrenci-asistani-olmanin-yararlari-ve-sorumluluklari" class="wp-block-heading">Avantages et responsabilités d&#8217;un assistant étudiant</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Devenir assistant étudiant présente de nombreux avantages. Ces avantages incluent des gains tant financiers qu&#8217;académiques.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Avantages</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Soutien financier :</strong> Les assistants étudiants reçoivent généralement une rémunération, ce qui aide à couvrir les frais de scolarité.</li>
<li><strong>Expérience académique :</strong> Ce rôle offre aux étudiants une expérience précieuse pour leur carrière académique.</li>
<li><strong>Réseautage :</strong> C&#8217;est l&#8217;occasion de rencontrer d&#8217;autres étudiants et des membres du corps professoral, et de se constituer un réseau professionnel.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Responsabilités</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Les assistants étudiants sont tenus d&#8217;accomplir certaines tâches. Parmi ces missions, on trouve :</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Préparation des notes de cours :</strong> Préparer des notes pour faciliter l&#8217;accès des étudiants au matériel de cours.</li>
<li><strong>Soutien à la recherche :</strong> Apporter un soutien dans les projets de recherche et collecter des données.</li>
<li><strong>Organisation d&#8217;événements étudiants :</strong> Aider à l&#8217;organisation d&#8217;activités sociales.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="ogrenci-asistanligi-ile-kulturel-deneyimlerinizi-gelistirin" class="wp-block-heading">Développez vos expériences culturelles grâce à l&#8217;assistanat étudiant</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">L&#8217;assistanat étudiant ne se limite pas à l&#8217;acquisition d&#8217;une expérience académique ; il enrichit également vos expériences culturelles. Travailler avec des étudiants de différentes cultures vous permet d&#8217;acquérir une perspective internationale.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Interaction culturelle</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Les assistants étudiants ont l&#8217;opportunité d&#8217;interagir avec d&#8217;autres étudiants venant de différents pays, favorisant ainsi les échanges culturels. C&#8217;est un excellent moyen de nouer de nouvelles amitiés et de comprendre différentes perspectives.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Participation aux événements locaux</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Les universités en Turquie proposent diverses activités culturelles aux étudiants. En tant qu&#8217;assistant étudiant, vous aurez l&#8217;occasion de participer à ces événements et d&#8217;aider à leur organisation. Par exemple, vous pourriez participer à des ateliers de cuisine traditionnelle turque ou organiser des festivals locaux.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyedeki-universitelerde-ogrenci-asistanligi-firsatlari" class="wp-block-heading">Opportunités d&#8217;assistanat étudiant dans les universités en Turquie</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">De nombreuses universités en Turquie offrent des opportunités d&#8217;assistanat étudiant. Ces opportunités sont généralement annoncées sur les sites web des départements concernés des universités. Voici quelques exemples de programmes d&#8217;assistanat étudiant dans des universités de premier plan :</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Boğaziçi Üniversitesi :</strong> Postes d&#8217;assistant de recherche et d&#8217;enseignement.</li>
<li><strong>ODTÜ :</strong> Opportunités d&#8217;assistanat dans divers départements académiques.</li>
<li><strong>İstanbul Teknik Üniversitesi :</strong> Assistanat étudiant dans les domaines de l&#8217;ingénierie et de l&#8217;architecture.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="sik-sorulan-sorular-faq" class="wp-block-heading">Foire Aux Questions (FAQ)</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Quels documents dois-je préparer pour devenir assistant étudiant en Turquie ?</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li>Pour devenir assistant étudiant, vous devrez généralement préparer les documents suivants :</li>
<li>Formulaire de candidature</li>
<li>CV à jour</li>
<li>Relevé de notes</li>
<li>Lettres de recommandation</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Où les postes d&#8217;assistant étudiant sont-ils annoncés ?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Les postes d&#8217;assistant étudiant sont généralement annoncés sur les sites web des départements concernés des universités et par les services des affaires étudiantes.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Quelles tâches puis-je assumer en tant qu&#8217;assistant étudiant ?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">En tant qu&#8217;assistant étudiant, vous pouvez être amené à préparer des notes de cours, à fournir un soutien à la recherche et à organiser des événements étudiants.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Quel soutien financier l&#8217;assistanat étudiant apporte-t-il ?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Bien que cela varie selon l&#8217;université, les postes d&#8217;assistant étudiant offrent généralement une rémunération mensuelle. Ce salaire peut vous aider à couvrir vos frais de scolarité.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Quels sont les avantages d&#8217;être un assistant étudiant en Turquie ?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Les avantages d&#8217;être un assistant étudiant incluent un soutien financier, l&#8217;acquisition d&#8217;une expérience académique et l&#8217;opportunité de se constituer un réseau professionnel.</p>', '$.wp_published_at', '2026-03-24T08:00:00Z', '$.wp_modified_at', '2026-03-14T15:45:41Z') WHERE "collection" = 'posts' AND "id" = ( SELECT "live_revision_id" FROM "ec_posts" WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'fr' AND "slug" = 'lassistanat-etudiant-et-les-roles-de-soutien-en-turquie' );
UPDATE "ec_posts" SET "source_seo" = '{"title":"Test Anxiety in Turkey and Coping Strategies - RoadtoStudy","description":"Discover effective methods for coping with test anxiety. Read now to learn how to manage stress and achieve your academic goals!","robots":"follow, index, max-snippet:-1, max-video-preview:-1, max-image-preview:large","ogTitle":"Test Anxiety in Turkey and Coping Strategies - RoadtoStudy","ogDescription":"Discover effective methods for coping with test anxiety. Read now to learn how to manage stress and achieve your academic goals!","ogImage":null,"twitterCard":"summary_large_image","twitterTitle":"Test Anxiety in Turkey and Coping Strategies - RoadtoStudy","twitterDescription":"Discover effective methods for coping with test anxiety. Read now to learn how to manage stress and achieve your academic goals!","canonicalPath":"/en/test-anxiety-in-turkey-and-coping-strategies/","hreflang":[{"hreflang":"tr","href":"/turkiyede-sinav-kaygisi/"},{"hreflang":"en","href":"/en/test-anxiety-in-turkey-and-coping-strategies/"},{"hreflang":"id","href":"/id/kecemasan-ujian-di-turki-dan-cara-mengatasinya/"},{"hreflang":"fr","href":"/fr/lanxiete-liee-aux-examens-en-turquie-et-les-methodes-pour-y-remedier/"}],"jsonLd":[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@graph":[{"@type":["Organization","Person"],"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","contentUrl":"https://roadtostudy.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Kare-Logo-e1740739634958.png","caption":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","inLanguage":"en-US","width":"450","height":"445"},"image":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/test-anxiety-in-turkey-and-coping-strategies/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/test-anxiety-in-turkey-and-coping-strategies/","name":"Test Anxiety in Turkey and Coping Strategies - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-05-23T14:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-05-23T14:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Test Anxiety in Turkey and Coping Strategies - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-05-23T14:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-05-23T14:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Health and Safety","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Discover effective methods for coping with test anxiety. Read now to learn how to manage stress and achieve your academic goals!","name":"Test Anxiety in Turkey and Coping Strategies - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/test-anxiety-in-turkey-and-coping-strategies/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/test-anxiety-in-turkey-and-coping-strategies/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/test-anxiety-in-turkey-and-coping-strategies/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Test anxiety is a common condition that many students face. Especially in Turkey, the intense competition and high expectations of the education system increase anxiety levels among students. In this article, we will discuss what test anxiety is, its causes, and methods for coping with it. We will also offer practical tips for managing test anxiety while studying in Turkey.</p>
<h2 id="sinav-kaygisi-nedir" class="wp-block-heading">What is Test Anxiety?</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Test anxiety is a state of excessive worry and stress felt before or during an exam. This anxiety can negatively affect a student&#8217;s performance and lower their exam scores. Test anxiety can manifest with physical symptoms (sweating, heart palpitations, nausea) and mental symptoms (difficulty concentrating, negative thoughts).</p>
<h2 id="sinav-kaygisinin-nedenleri-nelerdir" class="wp-block-heading">What Are the Causes of Test Anxiety?</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are many causes of test anxiety. These include:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>High Expectations:</strong> Pressure from family, teachers, or personal goals.</li>
<li><strong>Past Experiences:</strong> Negative experiences in previous exams.</li>
<li><strong>Feelings of Inadequacy:</strong> A lack of confidence in one&#8217;s own abilities.</li>
<li><strong>Lack of Preparation:</strong> Insufficient studying or a poor preparation process.</li>
</ul>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">These factors can increase students&#8217; anxiety levels during an exam and negatively impact their performance.</p>
<h2 id="sinav-kaygisiyla-basa-cikma-yontemleri-pratik-ipuclari" class="wp-block-heading">Coping with Test Anxiety: Practical Tips</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Here are some practical methods you can use to cope with test anxiety:</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">1. <strong>Regular Study:</strong> Create a planned <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/etkili-ders-calisma-teknikleri/">study schedule</a> and stick to it. This will help you feel more confident before the exam.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">2. <strong>Time Management:</strong> Allocate enough time to review subjects leading up to the exam date. This helps you avoid last-minute cramming.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">3. <strong>Emotional Support:</strong> Share your feelings with family and friends. Getting support can reduce anxiety.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">4. <strong>Physical Activity:</strong> Regular exercise lowers stress levels and improves mental health.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">5. <strong>Meditation and Breathing Exercises:</strong> Practicing relaxation techniques can reduce anxiety. For example, deep breathing or meditation is beneficial.</p>
<h2 id="zihin-oyunlari-sinav-kaygisini-yenmenin-psikolojik-yontemleri" class="wp-block-heading">Mindset Strategies: Psychological Methods to Overcome Test Anxiety</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Psychological methods are also very effective for managing test anxiety. These methods include:</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Developing Positive Thinking:</strong> Use positive self-talk. Motivate yourself with phrases like &#8220;I can do this.&#8221;</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Visualization Techniques:</strong> Visualize the exam moment and imagine yourself passing it successfully.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Confronting Anxiety:</strong> Confronting your anxieties can make them more manageable. Writing down your thoughts or <a href="https://psikologmerkezi.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">talking to a therapist can be helpful</a>.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyede-egitim-alirken-sinav-kaygisini-yonetmenin-yollari" class="wp-block-heading">Ways to Manage Test Anxiety While Studying in Turkey</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Here are some specific strategies for managing test anxiety while studying in Turkey:</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Support Services at Educational Institutions:</strong> Many universities offer psychological counseling services to students. Taking advantage of these services can reduce anxiety.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Group Study:</strong> Studying with your classmates increases knowledge sharing and provides social support.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Pre-Exam Preparation:</strong> Getting enough rest and a good night&#8217;s sleep the night before the exam can boost your performance.</p>
<h2 id="sinav-hazirligi-surecinde-kendinize-nasil-destek-olabilirsiniz" class="wp-block-heading">How to Support Yourself During Exam Preparation</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can apply these methods to support yourself during the exam preparation process:</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Regular Breaks:</strong> Balance your study sessions by scheduling regular breaks.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Nutrition:</strong> Eating a healthy diet improves your mental performance. It&#8217;s especially important to follow a balanced diet during exam periods.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">&#8211; <strong>Hobbies and Fun:</strong> Making time for your hobbies during exam preparation can reduce your stress levels. Doing activities you enjoy improves your mood.</p>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Test anxiety is a challenging experience for many students; however, it is possible to manage this anxiety with the right strategies. Methods like regular studying, positive thinking, and emotional support can reduce anxiety and improve your exam performance. While studying in Turkey, you can manage your test anxiety using the practical tips mentioned in this article and lead a successful academic life. Remember, every new exam is a learning opportunity, and you should be kind to yourself throughout the process.</p>
<h2 id="sik-sorulan-sorular-faq" class="wp-block-heading">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What methods can I use to cope with test anxiety in Turkey?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">To cope with test anxiety, you can use methods such as regular studying, time management, emotional support, physical activity, and meditation.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What are the causes of test anxiety?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">The causes of test anxiety include high expectations, past experiences, feelings of inadequacy, and a lack of preparation.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How can I support myself during the exam preparation process?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You can support yourself with methods like regular breaks, healthy eating, and making time for hobbies and fun.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">How do universities in Turkey support students with test anxiety?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Many universities help students manage test anxiety by offering psychological counseling services.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What psychological methods can I try to reduce test anxiety?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Psychological methods such as developing positive thinking, using visualization techniques, and confronting anxiety can help reduce test anxiety.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2026-05-23T11:00:00Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-16T19:52:29Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'test-anxiety-in-turkey-and-coping-strategies';
