/scientific-research-projects-and-funding-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}'), '$.content_html', '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">We will explore scientific research projects (BAP) in Turkey and their associated funding, examining how international students can take advantage of these opportunities.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyede-bilimsel-arastirma-projeleri-bap-nedir" class="wp-block-heading">What are Scientific Research Projects (BAP) in Turkey?</h2>
<p data-start="0" data-end="188">In Turkey, <strong data-start="11" data-end="49">Scientific Research Projects (BAP)</strong> are an institutional funding system designed to support the scientific work of academic staff at universities.</p>
<p data-start="0" data-end="188"><strong data-start="193" data-end="215">Key Features:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="218" data-end="858">
<li data-start="218" data-end="300">
<p data-start="220" data-end="300"><strong data-start="220" data-end="238">Legal Basis:</strong> Based on Article 58 of the Higher Education Law No. 2547.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="301" data-end="442">
<p data-start="303" data-end="442"><strong data-start="303" data-end="315">Management:</strong> Each university has a &#8220;BAP Commission&#8221; responsible for the approval, execution, and finalization of projects.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="443" data-end="594">
<p data-start="445" data-end="594"><strong data-start="445" data-end="454">Objective:</strong> To support <a href="https://roadtostudy.com/arastirma-izinleri-akademik-calismalar/">academic research</a> in universities and increase the number of national/international scientific publications and outputs.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="595" data-end="858">
<p data-start="597" data-end="626"><strong data-start="597" data-end="624">Supported Studies:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="629" data-end="858">
<li data-start="629" data-end="687">
<p data-start="631" data-end="687">Thesis projects (Master&#8217;s, PhD, medical specialty)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="690" data-end="719">
<p data-start="692" data-end="719">General research projects</p>
</li>
<li data-start="722" data-end="783">
<p data-start="724" data-end="783">Infrastructure projects (laboratory, equipment, software acquisition, etc.)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="786" data-end="822">
<p data-start="788" data-end="822">International collaboration projects</p>
</li>
<li data-start="825" data-end="858">
<p data-start="827" data-end="858">Strategic research projects</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="860" data-end="979"><strong data-start="863" data-end="877">Financing:</strong><br data-start="877" data-end="880" />It is covered by appropriations transferred from the central government budget to the universities&#8217; budgets each year.</p>
<h2 class="JlqpRe"><span class="JCzEY tNxQIb"><span class="CSkcDe">What Institutions Conduct Scientific Research in Turkey?</span></span></h2>
<p>In Turkey, scientific research is conducted by both <strong>public institutions</strong> and <strong>private research centers</strong>. Below, I have outlined the most important organizations:</p>
<h3>Public Institutions</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>TÜBİTAK (The Scientific and Technological Research Council of Turkey)</strong><br />
Turkey&#8217;s largest scientific research and project support institution; it operates research institutes and provides scholarships and funds.</li>
<li><strong>YÖK (Council of Higher Education)</strong> and <strong>Universities</strong><br />
They conduct scientific research through faculties, institutes, research centers, and <strong>BAP (Scientific Research Projects)</strong> units within universities.</li>
<li><strong>MAM (Marmara Research Center)</strong> – Affiliated with TÜBİTAK, it primarily works in the fields of engineering, energy, environment, materials, and chemistry.</li>
<li><strong>TÜBA (Turkish Academy of Sciences)</strong><br />
Supports scientific studies, publishes works, and presents awards to scientists.</li>
<li><strong>TÜSEB (Health Institutes of Turkey)</strong><br />
Conducts research in the fields of health, biotechnology, and drug development.</li>
<li><strong>TÜİK (Turkish Statistical Institute)</strong><br />
Conducts statistical research and provides data.</li>
<li><strong>Defense industry companies like ASELSAN, TUSAŞ, ROKETSAN</strong><br />
Conduct research in defense and technology.</li>
</ul>
<h3>In Health and Agriculture</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Ministry of Health Research Hospitals</strong><br />
Conduct clinical research.</li>
<li><strong>TAGEM (General Directorate of Agricultural Research and Policies of the Ministry of Agriculture and Forestry)</strong><br />
Conducts research in agriculture, livestock, and food.</li>
</ul>
<h3>International Collaborations</h3>
<ul>
<li>Turkey also participates in research through international funds like the <strong>European Union&#8217;s Horizon Europe</strong> program.</li>
<li>Knowledge transfer is supported through joint university-industry projects.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Private Institutions and Foundations</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Sabancı University Nanotechnology Research and Application Center (SUNUM)</strong></li>
<li><strong>Koç University Research Centers</strong></li>
<li>Research units of foundation universities such as <strong>Vehbi Koç Foundation, Sabancı Foundation, and Istanbul Kültür University Research Centers</strong></li>
<li><strong>R&#038;D centers</strong> of some private companies (Arçelik, Vestel, Ford Otosan, etc.)</li>
</ul>
