<h2 id="sik-sorulan-sorular" class="wp-block-heading">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What statistical methods are used in data analysis?</h3>
<p><strong>Descriptive</strong> (mean, standard deviation) and <strong>inferential</strong> (t-Test, ANOVA, Correlation, Regression) statistics are used.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What are the methods of data analysis?</h3>
<p><strong>Quantitative</strong> (statistical tests) and <strong>Qualitative</strong> (content/thematic analysis) methods. The goal is to summarize data, find relationships, and interpret them.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What are data processing methods?</h3>
<p>These are preparatory steps for analysis, such as <strong>data cleaning</strong> (removing missing/erroneous data), <strong>transformation</strong> (normalization), and <strong>reduction</strong> (factor analysis).</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What is statistical data analysis?</h3>
